SigLIP image encoder
---------------------

This product includes the Core ML conversion of Google's SigLIP-Base-
Patch16-224 image encoder, derived from:

    https://huggingface.co/google/siglip-base-patch16-224

Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. The full license text is
included alongside this NOTICE at `Vendor/siglip/licenses/LICENSE`.

The original model is described in:

    "Sigmoid Loss for Language Image Pre-Training"
    Zhai et al., ICCV 2023, https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.15343

Source for the conversion: `Scripts/convert-siglip-coreml.py` traces the
HuggingFace transformers checkpoint with PyTorch and emits a Core ML
.mlpackage (fp16 precision, normalization baked into ct.ImageType). The
emitted artifact ships in this repo at
`Vendor/siglip/models/SigLIP-Base-224_image.mlpackage` and is bundled
into the Mac app under `Youty.app/Contents/Resources/`.
